WEBVTT

00:02.453 --> 00:03.636
- Oh. Hey, look, Mandy.
- Huh?

00:03.671 --> 00:05.071
What a surprise.

00:05.089 --> 00:07.957
The parking citation people
are reaching out to us again.

00:08.007 --> 00:10.977
Okay, but, mama,
it totally wasn't my fault.

00:11.011 --> 00:12.278
Let me guess.
Was the meter maid jealous

00:12.312 --> 00:14.080
of your leather coat again?

00:14.098 --> 00:16.432
No. My tall boots.

00:17.851 --> 00:19.552
Look, you've been very
irresponsible with this car.

00:19.586 --> 00:21.387
One more strike,
and you lose it.

00:21.421 --> 00:22.263
Oh, come on. Everyone hates
on the pretty girl.

00:22.264 --> 00:23.106
Yeah.

00:23.140 --> 00:26.459
You two have no idea
how easy you've got it.

00:28.112 --> 00:30.279
Hey, honey, did we have
a party I was unaware of?

00:30.314 --> 00:31.314
No.

00:31.365 --> 00:33.132
That's weird.

00:33.167 --> 00:34.283
- What?
- Our trash cans were filled

00:34.318 --> 00:37.670
with wine bottles and what
I hope is onion dip.

00:37.705 --> 00:40.640
You think it's, uh,
you think it's the girls?

00:40.674 --> 00:41.641
No, baby.

00:41.675 --> 00:43.242
I think our kids like
corn liquor.

00:43.276 --> 00:46.295
Well...

00:46.330 --> 00:47.830
Joking aside,
I think you should give

00:47.881 --> 00:50.683
another one of those
drugs and alcohol talks anyway.

00:50.718 --> 00:52.468
It can't hurt.
Now why am I doing that?

00:52.503 --> 00:53.986
Well, because that's what
we decided...

00:54.021 --> 00:56.422
that, uh, you would be in charge
of the drugs and alcohol

00:56.456 --> 00:58.624
and I would be in charge
of the sex talk.

00:58.642 --> 01:00.626
That went well.

01:00.644 --> 01:04.797
Only one girl got pregnant
behind a bowling alley.

01:04.831 --> 01:08.768
Captioned by
closed captioning services, inc.

01:12.156 --> 01:14.040
Oh, hey, Michelle.

01:14.074 --> 01:15.274
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:15.308 --> 01:16.609
I hope you don't mind
if I use your trash cans.

01:16.643 --> 01:17.994
I ran out of room in mine.

01:18.028 --> 01:20.780
Oh, no. Oh, so that's where
the onion dip came from.

01:20.814 --> 01:23.916
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

01:23.951 --> 01:25.384
It, uh, looks like
you had a party.

01:25.419 --> 01:29.388
No, no. These are just
from a social gathering I had

01:29.423 --> 01:32.191
at my house with a bunch
of people.

01:32.226 --> 01:35.328
Well, you don't have to explain
yourself to me.

01:36.663 --> 01:39.432
Were the, uh,
were the Wongs invited?

01:39.466 --> 01:40.967
Yeah.

01:41.001 --> 01:42.635
- The Kanes?
- Yes.

01:42.669 --> 01:44.470
The Kopelmans?
Uh, you wouldn't have invited

01:44.505 --> 01:46.472
the Kopelmans
without inviting us.

01:48.008 --> 01:50.710
Uh...

01:52.513 --> 01:53.813
Dad, we've heard this speech.

01:53.847 --> 01:55.064
I know, and you're gonna
hear it again.

01:55.115 --> 01:56.816
Listen, I'm not gonna lie
to you.

01:56.850 --> 02:00.520
Drugs can make you feel
like you're on top of the world,

02:00.554 --> 02:03.523
like you can be the best
you can be and do anything,

02:03.557 --> 02:05.374
but... and here's
the big "but"...

02:05.409 --> 02:09.461
we have slipped
below the Kopelmans!

02:09.496 --> 02:13.082
All right, listen, the big "but"
here is that drugs can...

02:13.133 --> 02:16.502
I'm upset.
Could you follow me in here?

02:17.721 --> 02:19.972
I haven't got to the bad part
about the drugs yet,

02:20.007 --> 02:22.374
so you guys stay put,
and I'll back here in a minute

02:22.392 --> 02:26.679
with a really scary metaphor
about eggs fryin' in a pan.

02:29.716 --> 02:30.766
Honey, I haven't got
to the dangerous part

02:30.818 --> 02:32.618
about drugs yet.

02:32.653 --> 02:35.721
Michelle had a party,
and she didn't invite us.

02:35.756 --> 02:37.290
So we dodged a bullet.

02:37.324 --> 02:39.625
No. Wait.

02:39.660 --> 02:41.427
I have known Michelle
for years...

02:41.461 --> 02:42.778
- Right.
- And when Eve was born,

02:42.830 --> 02:44.947
I almost named her "Michelle,"
until I realized that

02:44.998 --> 02:47.066
that was the name
of your college girlfriend.

02:48.335 --> 02:49.969
Yeah, she... she was
a cheerleader.

02:50.003 --> 02:53.339
All right, stop.
You know what? Stop. Just...

02:58.579 --> 03:01.614
I mean, I just... I-I cannot
wrap my head around this.

03:01.648 --> 03:03.416
I mean, what... what could I
possibly have done

03:03.450 --> 03:04.634
to offend her?

03:04.685 --> 03:06.252
We were just at
her theme party last month...

03:06.270 --> 03:07.345
Yeah.

03:07.346 --> 03:08.421
And I... I thought that went great.
Remember?

03:08.455 --> 03:09.755
Yeah, I remember.

03:15.445 --> 03:19.765
Oh. Michelle.
This is your best party <i>ever.</i>

03:19.783 --> 03:21.600
Oh, I just love the '70s theme.

03:21.618 --> 03:23.152
Of course, I was just
a baby back then.

03:23.203 --> 03:25.104
Yeah, an eighth-grade baby.

03:25.138 --> 03:27.273
Wah, wah.

03:27.291 --> 03:29.275
Oh. Lava lamps are such
a nice touch...

03:29.293 --> 03:30.276
Yeah. Cool.
Right?

03:30.294 --> 03:32.111
Well, as one scientist
to another,

03:32.129 --> 03:34.347
I really try to have
an eye for detail.

03:34.381 --> 03:37.783
Ah. Well, I'm gonna go, uh,
check out the fondue bar.

03:39.119 --> 03:41.470
Michelle
Aren't you a weather girl?

03:41.505 --> 03:42.955
Meteorologist.

03:42.973 --> 03:44.957
<i>TV</i> meteorologist.
You just point at clouds

03:44.975 --> 03:46.842
that aren't really there.
"Look over here

03:46.894 --> 03:48.527
at the green..."

03:49.629 --> 03:51.597
Uh, actually,
my profession requires

03:51.631 --> 03:53.799
an extraordinary degree
of skill and knowledge.

03:53.817 --> 03:55.101
Um, I... I wasn't being
insulting.

03:55.135 --> 03:57.069
I was just... just, you know,
bustin' your chops,

03:57.104 --> 03:59.305
but isn't it funny that
your whole job

03:59.323 --> 04:01.474
you could download
on a free app?

04:01.508 --> 04:04.477
I mean, the whole...

04:05.846 --> 04:09.282
Oh, boy.

04:11.118 --> 04:13.452
Mystery to me.

04:15.455 --> 04:18.040
Well, I mean, I-I didn't
write her a thank-you note.

04:18.091 --> 04:19.041
Do you think that
could be it?

04:19.091 --> 04:20.559
- Oh, definitely.
- I-I...

04:20.594 --> 04:22.962
Pfft. Come on.
Write her a thank-you note.

04:22.996 --> 04:25.264
Baby, you're better
than that.

04:29.169 --> 04:32.004
Mm-hmm. I see.

04:32.039 --> 04:34.040
Wow. Okay.

04:34.074 --> 04:36.809
Hey. You need to move your car.
I'm gonna shoot some hoops.

04:36.843 --> 04:38.544
Okay. Here.
You move it. Here.

04:38.578 --> 04:39.979
- I'm 13. I'm not allowed.
- I'm in the middle

04:40.013 --> 04:42.114
of a very important conversation
right now, okay?

04:42.149 --> 04:45.251
Well, do you think that
Jeanette shaves her forearms?

04:45.285 --> 04:46.652
Give me the keys.

04:46.686 --> 04:47.920
I was thinking so, too,
because, to tell you the truth,

04:47.955 --> 04:49.588
you can see fuzz all the way
down to her elbows,

04:49.623 --> 04:51.857
and then it's, like,
nothing.

04:51.892 --> 04:53.592
- Mandy.
- Uh-huh.

04:53.627 --> 04:56.095
Mandy, you were supposed
to empty the dishwasher.

04:56.129 --> 04:59.999
You were supposed to go
to college. Oh!

05:00.033 --> 05:01.217
Did you just hear that?

05:01.251 --> 05:02.385
I was just totally funny.

05:02.419 --> 05:03.719
My sister walks in
and she's all,

05:03.754 --> 05:05.604
"um, Mandy, you were supposed
to empty the dishwasher,"

05:05.639 --> 05:06.889
and then I was like...
hey, hey, hey...

05:06.923 --> 05:09.425
"you were supposed to go
to college." Ow!

05:10.777 --> 05:12.094
I gotta call you back.

05:13.480 --> 05:14.747
How did this happen?

05:14.781 --> 05:15.931
How do you think
it happened?

05:15.983 --> 05:17.950
I'm 13. I've never driven
a car before.

05:17.985 --> 05:19.268
Oh, how hard can it be?

05:19.319 --> 05:23.022
YouTube is full of videos
of dogs driving tractors!

05:23.056 --> 05:24.590
Mom and dad are gonna
kill me.

05:24.624 --> 05:26.559
I've never been
in trouble before <i>ever.</i>

05:26.593 --> 05:28.728
I'm not like you people.

05:29.896 --> 05:31.230
You can take the hit
for this one,

05:31.264 --> 05:32.832
because I am one strike away
from public transportation.

05:32.866 --> 05:34.300
No. No. No, no, no.
You could...

05:34.334 --> 05:35.434
you could walk...

05:35.469 --> 05:37.269
Or... or you...
or you could ride your bike.

05:39.740 --> 05:41.374
I'm sorry.
Now I'm just being mean.

05:41.408 --> 05:42.741
You know what?

05:42.759 --> 05:44.577
This... this is your fault
for making me drive <i>your</i> car.

05:44.611 --> 05:46.212
It's your fault
for always exercising.

05:46.246 --> 05:48.547
This is America, Eve.
Kids don't do that.

05:48.582 --> 05:49.782
All right. That's enough.
Enough, okay?

05:49.816 --> 05:51.183
I have an idea. Come here.

05:51.218 --> 05:53.919
Look, Kyle has this device
that takes dents out of cars.

05:53.937 --> 05:55.788
He uses it, like, twice a day.

05:55.822 --> 05:58.824
His apartment's across
the street from a driving range.

05:58.859 --> 05:59.892
Hey, guys.

05:59.926 --> 06:01.394
What's with all the noise
out here?

06:01.428 --> 06:02.895
Um...

06:02.929 --> 06:04.563
We were just gonna...

06:04.598 --> 06:07.166
Clean the garage
as a surprise, daddy.

06:07.200 --> 06:09.969
Oh. Well,
use my power washer.

06:10.003 --> 06:12.271
Plug it in. You can get
the grease stains off the floor.

06:12.305 --> 06:14.206
Thanks.

06:16.109 --> 06:18.244
Even Cinderella didn't have
to power-wash the garage.

06:23.800 --> 06:25.451
Did I track something in?

06:26.619 --> 06:29.889
Just got off
the phone with Michelle.

06:29.923 --> 06:32.258
Did you know her entire job
could be done

06:32.292 --> 06:34.994
by a 99-cent phone app?

06:37.197 --> 06:40.232
Of course you did!

06:42.819 --> 06:46.372
Actually, I-I said it was
a free app,

06:46.406 --> 06:50.976
but that probably doesn't,
uh, help right now, does it?

06:50.994 --> 06:53.028
Why would you even say
something like that?

06:53.080 --> 06:54.547
Michelle is my friend.

06:54.581 --> 06:57.183
'Cause she's
an accuweather-ologist.

06:57.217 --> 07:00.169
She's wrong half the time,
but she still has a job.

07:00.203 --> 07:02.922
I just... it's the truth.

07:02.956 --> 07:04.256
All right. You know what?
Could...

07:04.291 --> 07:06.559
could you just make an effort
to not insult our friends?

07:06.593 --> 07:08.677
Well, at this age,
maybe we need less friends.

07:08.712 --> 07:10.930
We could thin the herd out
a little bit.

07:10.964 --> 07:12.398
You're thinning the people
that I like.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.400
I mean, Michelle and I...
we do fun things together.

07:14.434 --> 07:16.335
We go to the book groups
and the art fairs

07:16.353 --> 07:18.471
and... and that
soups of autumns class

07:18.505 --> 07:19.838
a-at the learning annex.

07:19.856 --> 07:22.575
Right. In my opinion, that was
a complete waste of $6.

07:22.609 --> 07:26.512
All right. You know what?
The girls are getting older,

07:26.546 --> 07:28.898
and if we don't maintain
our social life,

07:28.949 --> 07:31.584
we are staring down
the barrel

07:31.618 --> 07:36.355
of <i>decades</i>
of just you and me.

07:38.792 --> 07:39.909
And you wanna know
who I'm dragging

07:39.960 --> 07:42.228
to that
soups of autumn class?

07:43.296 --> 07:44.296
I'll be dead before then.

07:44.331 --> 07:46.866
Oh, no, no, no, no.
No, you won't,

07:46.900 --> 07:51.837
because I will keep you alive
long enough to suffer through...

07:51.872 --> 07:53.772
All of it.

08:00.147 --> 08:03.549
