car door panel dings.

13:27.143 --> 13:29.344
I was actually talking
about you.

13:29.378 --> 13:30.879
Mandy, he's trying to help.

13:30.913 --> 13:32.147
Just carry on, Kyle.

13:32.181 --> 13:34.516
All right.

13:34.550 --> 13:35.717
Yes!
Ohh.

13:35.751 --> 13:37.135
- It's perfect!
- Ohh!

13:37.186 --> 13:38.553
Yes. Yes!

13:38.587 --> 13:40.388
13 years, 16 weeks,
and 4 days

13:40.423 --> 13:42.023
of mom and dad
not getting mad at me.

13:42.058 --> 13:43.024
My record stands.

13:44.060 --> 13:45.560
Great.

13:49.432 --> 13:51.650
Yeah.

13:51.701 --> 13:53.401
That sometimes happens.

14:02.724 --> 14:04.758
I love kelp.

14:05.810 --> 14:07.394
Mmm. Oh, my God.

14:07.428 --> 14:08.595
The only thing that would
make it better is

14:08.613 --> 14:09.763
if it was a cheeseburger.

14:09.781 --> 14:12.533
And if these
were onion rings

14:12.567 --> 14:13.634
instead of beet chips.

14:14.936 --> 14:17.103
Oh, come on, you guys.
Be adventurous.

14:18.122 --> 14:19.105
Yeah.
Yeah, I've always wondered

14:19.123 --> 14:20.457
what it would be like
to be a rabbit

14:20.491 --> 14:24.011
running through the forest
with its mouth open.

14:26.080 --> 14:27.130
That's Outdoor Man talking.

14:27.165 --> 14:28.465
- That's right.
- Yeah.

14:28.499 --> 14:30.817
You know, Michelle, I am so glad
we could make this happen.

14:30.852 --> 14:32.085
- Me, too...
- Yeah.

14:32.119 --> 14:33.954
And I'm so happy
everyone's just...

14:33.972 --> 14:36.790
Trying.

14:36.824 --> 14:38.425
What do you mean by that?

14:38.459 --> 14:39.626
Honey, kelp...
put it in your mouth.

14:43.297 --> 14:45.148
Tom, I understand
you were a Navy S.E.A.L.

14:45.183 --> 14:46.183
Oh, he doesn't like
to talk about it.

14:46.234 --> 14:48.669
Hell, yeah, I was!

14:48.703 --> 14:50.237
Well, here's a toast...

14:50.271 --> 14:52.189
To the men
and women that keep us free.

14:52.240 --> 14:53.490
- Oh.
- And... and this is what?

14:53.524 --> 14:54.841
Cashew milk.

14:54.876 --> 14:56.276
Wow.

14:56.310 --> 14:58.478
<i>Semper fi.</i> Do or die.

14:59.781 --> 15:01.314
<i>Semper fi?</i>

15:01.332 --> 15:02.950
- Um, Vanessa...
- Uh...

15:02.984 --> 15:04.201
- Yeah.
- I'm gonna use the ladies' room. Wanna come with?

15:04.252 --> 15:05.202
- Of course. Yeah.
- Mm.

15:05.253 --> 15:06.286
- Yeah. Excuse us.
- All right, ladies. Good.

15:07.789 --> 15:10.424
Yes.

15:10.458 --> 15:12.125
Wow. It seems our menfolk
are really getting along...

15:12.159 --> 15:13.493
Yeah, yeah. Doesn't it?

15:13.511 --> 15:14.494
And Mike has changed.

15:14.512 --> 15:15.495
He's less...

15:15.530 --> 15:16.797
Um... cranky?

15:16.831 --> 15:17.798
I was gonna say "honest."

15:17.832 --> 15:19.683
Honest. Yeah, me, too.

15:19.717 --> 15:21.435
You know, I was mad
about his app comment...

15:21.469 --> 15:24.104
- Mm-hmm.
- But I'll let you in on a little secret.

15:24.138 --> 15:27.524
That's how
I get a lot of my information.

15:27.558 --> 15:29.810
But it's how
you present it.

15:29.844 --> 15:30.978
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

15:33.197 --> 15:35.949
On that final push to Baghdad,
I drove that M1

15:35.984 --> 15:38.351
18 hours straight
without stopping.

15:38.369 --> 15:40.921
Drove an M1
for 18 hours, huh?

15:40.955 --> 15:42.189
That's a long time.

15:42.223 --> 15:43.523
You're telling me.

15:43.558 --> 15:45.392
- Yeah.
- I lived it.

15:45.426 --> 15:48.462
Yeah. You know what

15:48.496 --> 15:49.529
I'm gonna call my daughters,
see if they're all right.

15:49.547 --> 15:50.664
Yeah. Sure.

15:50.698 --> 15:51.915
We should hang out
more often.

15:51.966 --> 15:53.200
- Yeah.
- Maybe something at the learning annex.

15:53.234 --> 15:55.218
Oh, you know what? They have
a new class on pickling.

15:55.253 --> 15:56.753
Did you know
that pickling is back?

15:56.804 --> 15:58.755
- I didn't, but it doesn't shock me.
- I... yeah.

15:58.806 --> 16:00.090
Hey, guys.

16:00.141 --> 16:01.575
- Yeah.
- Uh, could I talk to you privately for a minute?

16:01.609 --> 16:02.559
It'll just take a second.

16:02.593 --> 16:04.177
- Oh, of course. Uh-huh.
- Thanks.

16:04.211 --> 16:05.345
- Hey, uh...
- Yeah. Hey. Yeah.

16:05.379 --> 16:06.480
What's going on?

16:06.514 --> 16:08.515
Um, listen,
I think that guy's a liar.

16:08.549 --> 16:09.616
I don't think
he'S a Navy S.E.A.L.

16:09.651 --> 16:10.851
I think
he's just full of it.

16:10.885 --> 16:11.902
- He just told me he was...
- Ohh.

16:11.936 --> 16:14.271
In an M1A1 Abrams tank
for 18 hours.

16:14.322 --> 16:15.405
- It's impossible.
- Look. Come on. Come on.

16:15.440 --> 16:17.074
Maybe... maybe he drank
a lot of coffee.

16:17.108 --> 16:20.694
Maybe he peed in a jug.
We don't know. We weren't there.

16:20.728 --> 16:22.596
He wasn't there either.
The S. E.A.L.S... they...

16:22.630 --> 16:23.914
they don't drive
tanks around.

16:23.948 --> 16:25.282
- Even if they did... 18 hours?
- Okay.

16:25.333 --> 16:26.950
- It has a short fuel window.
- All right. Y...

16:27.001 --> 16:28.769
it would only be about four to six
hours top speed with... - uh, wh...

16:28.803 --> 16:31.421
why do you have to know
these things

16:31.456 --> 16:32.439
You know, it's against
the law what he's doing.

16:32.473 --> 16:34.041
- Oh, yeah.
- Stolen valor act.

16:34.075 --> 16:35.709
- Old red there could get six months in jail...
- Okay, but...

16:35.743 --> 16:36.960
- For doing that.
- Mike, listen. No, no. L...

16:37.011 --> 16:38.095
we talked about this.
You don't have to say

16:38.129 --> 16:40.130
- the truth all the time.
- So you're...

16:40.214 --> 16:41.615
- you don't. You don't, so... - you're
making me pick between wife and country?

16:41.649 --> 16:44.134
All right, so, look,
look...

16:44.185 --> 16:46.053
I will make it worth
your while. I...

16:46.087 --> 16:48.155
I will do the thing that
you're always asking me to do,

16:48.189 --> 16:51.625
but I won't do it because it
makes me physically sick.

16:54.162 --> 16:57.964
You will root for Michigan
over Ohio state?

16:57.999 --> 17:01.068
Yeah.

17:01.102 --> 17:03.236
I can't believe
mom and dad are gonna

17:03.271 --> 17:05.571
take you away from me...

17:05.606 --> 17:07.339
Just when I finally figured out
how to move the mirrors

17:07.375 --> 17:10.577
and what that little
red warning light was for.

17:10.611 --> 17:13.180
Hey, where's
dad's duffel bag?

17:13.214 --> 17:14.513
I don't know. Why?

17:14.549 --> 17:18.452
I'm gonna pack some stuff.
I think I'm moving on.

17:18.486 --> 17:20.654
Eve, what are you
talking about?

17:20.688 --> 17:23.423
I want mom and dad
to remember me how I was...

17:23.458 --> 17:27.794
innocent,
perfect, their final hope.

17:29.630 --> 17:32.432
I'm gonna head down South,
look for work.

17:32.467 --> 17:35.435
I'll be in touch
when I get settled.

17:35.470 --> 17:38.638
Gosh, I'm gonna
miss this place.

17:38.673 --> 17:40.474
Shut up.
You're not going anywhere.

17:40.508 --> 17:41.575
How do you know?

17:41.609 --> 17:42.576
Because you miss
one homework assignment,

17:42.610 --> 17:44.111
you break out in hives.

17:44.145 --> 17:46.780
Oh. Dad gave us homework.
We're supposed to read

17:46.814 --> 17:48.482
this drug literature.
Yeah, I wouldn't sweat it.

17:48.516 --> 17:50.784
It's mostly just cartoons
and a bunch of stickers.

17:51.986 --> 17:53.620
I just got a great idea.

17:54.689 --> 17:58.158
Sadness makes
my eyes sparkle.

17:59.327 --> 18:00.994
What?

18:02.330 --> 18:05.265
So there I was,

18:05.299 --> 18:07.467
limping through the streets
of Baghdad,

18:07.502 --> 18:09.402
dragging my wounded leg,

18:09.437 --> 18:11.905
sniper fire everywhere.

18:11.939 --> 18:13.557
We barely made it out
alive.

18:13.608 --> 18:15.008
Unbelievable.

18:15.042 --> 18:17.043
Yeah, she said it.

18:18.846 --> 18:20.647
Was the longest night
of my life.

18:20.681 --> 18:22.382
I know just what you mean.

18:22.416 --> 18:24.251
Then they got me on a bird

18:24.285 --> 18:26.086
and medevaced me out
of there at first light.

18:26.120 --> 18:27.721
Then I had four months

18:27.755 --> 18:29.656
of pretty intense physical therapy.
Mm.

18:29.690 --> 18:31.391
Yeah

18:31.425 --> 18:32.392
Doesn't matter. Leave it.

18:32.426 --> 18:34.594
Just leave it.
Oh, no. Let him talk.

18:34.629 --> 18:38.064
It was back at home base.
Fort Douglas.

18:38.099 --> 18:39.533
In Utah?

18:39.567 --> 18:40.934
You know, honey,
it's getting late.

18:40.968 --> 18:41.935
- We should, uh, we should get going.
- No, you know...

18:41.969 --> 18:42.936
- Oh.
- Yeah.

18:42.970 --> 18:43.937
We got
plenty more war stories.

18:43.971 --> 18:45.672
We gotta honor
our soldiers, honey.

18:45.706 --> 18:48.942
No, Vanessa's right.
I gotta get up early tomorrow.

18:48.976 --> 18:50.760
Well, I guess we'll see
you two at the party.

18:50.812 --> 18:51.945
Tom, no.

18:51.979 --> 18:53.446
There... there's a party?

18:53.481 --> 18:55.515
Great.
What, uh, what can we bring?

18:55.549 --> 18:59.119
Oh, yeah.
It's not really a party.

18:59.153 --> 19:01.021
Uh, it's just
a few close friends.

19:01.055 --> 19:02.189
Will the Wongs be there?

19:02.223 --> 19:03.623
- Uh...
- The Kanes?

19:03.658 --> 19:04.891
- Uh...
- The Kopelmans?

19:04.926 --> 19:06.526
Uh...
Seriously?

19:06.561 --> 19:08.862
But...
I don't understand.

19:08.896 --> 19:10.630
May I speak freely?
Please.

19:10.665 --> 19:12.566
The Kopelmans
don't like you.

19:12.600 --> 19:15.468
So... pssh, don't invite
the Kopelmans...

19:15.503 --> 19:17.170
Right?

19:17.205 --> 19:18.638
It's complicated.

19:18.673 --> 19:21.041
We're very close with them.

19:21.075 --> 19:24.578
I guess
it's not that complicated.

19:24.612 --> 19:28.465
I see. I see. Uh, well,
no, I-I understand.

19:28.516 --> 19:29.583
Yeah.

19:29.617 --> 19:31.051
Just, uh, no hard feelings.

19:31.085 --> 19:32.052
No.

19:33.955 --> 19:37.257
Mike... do it.

19:40.645 --> 19:42.762
You're not a Navy S.E.A.L.

19:42.797 --> 19:44.264
Ohh.

19:44.282 --> 19:47.601
That is the first full breath
I've had all night.

19:47.635 --> 19:49.602
Not a Navy S.E.A.L.? Of course he is.
No. Not a Navy S.E.A.L.

19:49.620 --> 19:50.820
He doesn't know
what he's talking about.

19:50.872 --> 19:51.905
You don't know what
you're talking about.

19:51.939 --> 19:53.773
Fort Douglas...
that's an army base.

19:53.791 --> 19:55.275
It was closed 20 years ago.

19:55.309 --> 19:56.776
<i>Semper fi...</i>
that's from the marine corps,

19:56.811 --> 19:57.961
as I recall.

19:57.995 --> 20:00.113
M1 tank doesn't have
an 18-hour range.

20:00.131 --> 20:01.631
You don't know anything
about what you're talking...

20:01.666 --> 20:04.217
plus I don't think the S.E.A.L.s
use self-Tanner, do they?

20:04.252 --> 20:05.518
Night, folks.

20:05.553 --> 20:07.787
Come on.

20:07.822 --> 20:09.506
Oh, oh, oh, oh!

20:09.557 --> 20:11.791
And she gets
all her weather information

20:11.826 --> 20:13.960
from a free phone app.

20:13.978 --> 20:16.463
It's true.

20:20.668 --> 20:22.836
I cannot believe
I said that to her.

20:22.870 --> 20:25.605
I mean, that could ruin
her career. Just...

20:25.640 --> 20:26.606
But it felt good.

20:26.641 --> 20:29.309
Oh, yeah. Yeah, yeah.

20:29.327 --> 20:33.313
It really did. Yeah. Oh.

20:33.347 --> 20:34.647
You know, I-I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

20:34.665 --> 20:36.182
I know I'm supposed
to be the civilized part

20:36.217 --> 20:38.485
of this couple.

20:38.519 --> 20:39.986
- You don't need to apologize for being...
- I just...

20:40.004 --> 20:42.188
More like me.

20:42.223 --> 20:43.990
You know, honey,

20:44.025 --> 20:46.159
we are gonna grow old
alone together,

20:46.193 --> 20:47.827
just you and I.

20:47.862 --> 20:49.462
Promise?

20:49.497 --> 20:50.463
Yeah.

20:50.497 --> 20:52.732
- Mm.
- Ohh.

20:52.767 --> 20:54.000
- I gotta eat somethin' cooked.
- Mm.

20:54.035 --> 20:55.936
I swear I do.

21:02.026 --> 21:05.629
Wow. Look at that.

21:07.865 --> 21:08.998
Interesting.

21:09.017 --> 21:11.101
Yeah. Oh, Mike,
we've got some good girls.

21:11.135 --> 21:12.469
Yeah,
we've got some good girls.

21:12.503 --> 21:14.204
Yeah. They're just...
they're gonna grow up,

21:14.238 --> 21:15.772
go out in the world,
and do just fine.

21:15.807 --> 21:17.140
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

21:17.175 --> 21:21.311
I think they pulled a dent out
and the paint popped off.

21:21.346 --> 21:23.647
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, that makes more sense.

21:23.681 --> 21:24.715
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

21:24.749 --> 21:26.249
Ohh. What should we do
about it?

21:26.284 --> 21:27.650
Nothing.

